---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — guitarserials.org" description="About guitarserials.org: a free, open-source guitar serial-number decoder.">
  <div class="prose max-w-2xl py-8 dark:prose-invert">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">About</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      guitarserials.org is a free, accurate, open-source guitar serial-number decoder. It replaces
      scattered forum posts and outdated PDFs with a single well-researched reference.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What it does</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Given a serial number and a brand, the decoder identifies the format era and decodes the
      production year where the format encodes it. Every rule is derived from authoritative
      sources (manufacturer documentation, published references, photographic evidence on known
      instruments) and checked with a test suite that runs on every change.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How it runs</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      The matcher is pure TypeScript (<code>@guitarserials/core</code>, on npm) with zero runtime
      dependencies. The site is a static Astro build — every decode runs in your browser. Nothing
      is uploaded, nothing is logged.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Contributing</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Found an incorrect decode, or know a brand/format we should add? Open a report on GitHub.
      New brand support requires at least two authoritative sources cited per format claim, plus
      test cases for every rule. See <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code> for details.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">License</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      MIT. Use it, fork it, embed it — attribution is appreciated.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
